            <h2 style="padding-left: 10px;">CSS Basics:</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Introduction to CSS and its role in web development.</li>
                <li>CSS syntax and selectors.</li>
                <li>Inline styles, internal stylesheets, and external stylesheets.</li>
                <li>CSS box model: margin, padding, border, and content.</li>
                <li>CSS color properties and values.</li>
            </ol>
            <h2 style="padding-left: 10px;">CSS Selectors and Specificity:</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Understanding different types of CSS selectors: element selectors, class selectors, ID selectors, attribute selectors, etc.</li>
                <li>Specificity rules and how they determine which styles are applied.</li>
                <li>Combining selectors using descendant selectors, child selectors, sibling selectors, etc.</li>
                <li>Pseudo-classes and pseudo-elements.</li>
            </ol>
            <h2 style="padding-left: 10px;">CSS Layout and Positioning:</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Building layouts using CSS: block, inline, and inline-block elements.</li>
                <li>Positioning elements: static, relative, absolute, fixed, and sticky.</li>
                <li>Floats and clearing floats.</li>
                <li>CSS flexbox for flexible layouts.</li>
                <li>CSS grid for grid-based layouts.</li>
            </ol>
            <h2 style="padding-left: 10px;">CSS Typography:</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Styling text with CSS: font-family, font-size, font-weight, etc.</li>
                <li>Text formatting: color, text-decoration, text-align, text-transform, etc.</li>
                <li>Working with web fonts and Google Fonts.</li>
                <li>Creating responsive typography.</li>
            </ol>
            <h2 style="padding-left: 10px;">CSS Box Model and Layout:</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Understanding the CSS box model: margin, padding, border, and content.</li>
                <li>Box sizing: content-box and border-box.</li>
                <li>Box shadows and rounded corners.</li>
                <li>Creating responsive and fluid layouts.</li>
            </ol>
            <h2 style="padding-left: 10px;">CSS Transitions and Animations:</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>CSS transitions for smooth state changes.</li>
                <li>CSS animations for creating animated effects.</li>
                <li>Keyframes and animation properties.</li>
                <li>Timing functions and easing.</li>
            </ol>
            <h2 style="padding-left: 10px;">CSS Media Queries:</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Building responsive designs with media queries.</li>
                <li>Targeting different devices and screen sizes.</li>
                <li>Mobile-first vs. desktop-first approaches.</li>
                <li>Media query best practices.</li>
            </ol>   
            <h2 style="padding-left: 10px;">CSS Frameworks:</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Introduction to popular CSS frameworks like Bootstrap, Foundation, and Bulma.</li>
                <li>Using pre-built CSS components and grids.</li>
                <li>Customizing and extending CSS frameworks.</li>
            </ol>
